Post-COVID-19: minimally important difference survey

Post-COVID-19: minimally important difference survey

  • Results
    • Participation
    • Survey results

S. Jain, J. Rylance and A. Chaillon

2024-10-22

WHO is seeking to refine our understanding of minimally important differences (MID) for Post COVID-19 Conditions. Minimally important differences are the smallest changes in outcomes or measurements that are considered significant enough by patients to indicate a noticeable improvement or worsening of a condition.

Results

Participation

A total of 42 (55%) participated to the survey.

WHO Arbovirus guideline – Minimally Important Difference survey1
